{"id":572922578,"lang":"python3","lang_name":"Python3","time":"2 years, 2 months","timestamp":1634519204,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"76 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/572922578/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Add Two Numbers","memory":"14.1 MB","code":"class Solution:\n    def addTwoNumbers(self, l1: ListNode, l2: ListNode) -> ListNode:\n        # first, convert both lists to arrays\n        l1arr = []\n        l2arr = []\n        while not (l1 == None and l2 == None):\n            if l1 != None:\n                l1arr.append(l1.val)\n                l1 = l1.next\n            if l2 != None:\n                l2arr.append(l2.val)\n                l2 = l2.next\n\n        # then, convert the arrays to ints\n        l1int = 0\n        l2int = 0\n        for i in range(len(l1arr)):\n            l1int += l1arr[i]*(10**i)\n        for i in range(len(l2arr)):\n            l2int += l2arr[i]*(10**i)\n\n        # get result, then convert back to linked list\n        resultint = l1int + l2int\n        result = ListNode()\n        resultit = result\n        while True:\n            resultit.val = resultint % 10\n\n            resultint //= 10\n            if resultint > 0:\n                resultit.next = ListNode()\n                resultit = resultit.next\n            else: break\n\n        return result","compare_result":"","title_slug":"add-two-numbers","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
